  <description><![CDATA[<p>Nestled amongst Olive groves and overlooking the crystalline waters of <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda">Lake Garda</a>, Hotel Internazionale is the perfect choice for those seeking tranquility and relaxation in one of Lake Garda's most affluent resorts. An enchanting and friendly atmosphere is created by the family who own and oversee the running of each day and this Italian familial atmosphere can be felt throughout. The décor is sleek and modern in the communal areas with rooms taking on a traditional and simplistic design with good amenities and many offering views of the majestic mountains surrounding the hotel. The natural gardens are home to a large infinity pool from which you can enjoy unrivaled and uninterrupted views of Lake Garda's indigo waters and <a data-udi="umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce" href="/{localLink:umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce}" title="Malcesine">Malcesine</a> castle to the west. Sun loungers and parasols are plentiful and provide the perfect spot to kick back and relax in the glorious Malcesine sunshine. For those wanting to escape the sunshine for a few hours, the indoor spa offers a selection of facilities including 2 whirlpools, sauna and solarium which can be booked and paid for locally. Breakfast is served each morning in the hotel's quaint and traditional dining room with both hot and cold options available such as freshly baked breads, cakes, pastries, eggs cooked to order, pancakes, bacon, cold cuts and local cheeses to help get your day started. Whilst this is a bed and breakfast property, lunch can be purchased locally from the onsite restaurant within the hotel bar and taken on the outdoor terrace. With the centre of Malcesine just a 10 minute stroll away its easy to get out and about, whether you're in the mood for strolling through the famous cobbled lanes of Malcesine or wanting to use the ferry to see its neighbouring and adjacent resorts of <a data-udi="umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c}" title="Limone">Limone</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01}" title="Riva">Riva</a> or you can spend a day by the lakeside which is just 3 minutes' from the hotel and live La Dolce Vita on the Malcesine promenade with an Aperol in hand. </p>]]></description>
